{
  "article_id": "LosAngelesTimes1928",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "One of the greatest honors it is possible to bestow on a human being—posthumous recognition—was awarded "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", \""
      },
      {
        "text": "The Lost Woman of San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ",\" when the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Daughters of the American Revolution",
        "entity_key": "daughters",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "led by "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Alfred Brosseau",
        "entity_key": "abr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", president-general, "
      },
      {
        "text": "mission fathers",
        "entity_key": "misfats",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "and laymen placed a plaque in her memory in the gardens of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "old mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_santabarbaramission",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "here. "
      },
      {
        "text": "And those who gathered for the ceremony heard once again the story of sacrifice and peril of ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the old woman",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The story told of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mission fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "pressing all "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_missionindians",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "into service in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and then recruiting the "
      },
      {
        "text": "island Indians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Because of its distance from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was left alone until 1835, when "
      },
      {
        "text": "the only large schooner on the coast",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and brought "
      },
      {
        "text": "the twenty surviving Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "away from "
      },
      {
        "text": "their native land",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "As they drew away from the shore, ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the women",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "realized that ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her baby",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was not on board, and after frantically appealing in vain to ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the captain",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "chu",
          "isp"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to turn back, she jumped overboard and disappeared in the waves.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The natives",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were distributed among ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the various missions",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "itself was wrecked near ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Golden Gate",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_thegoldengate",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "before an opportunity came to return for ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "who made such a sacrifice.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The woman of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "became part of the lore of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Spanish settlement here",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Fifteen years later, fishermen after sea otters reported having seen a figure running up and down the beach of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "again arousing interest in the legend of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the lost woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Capt. George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", whose "
      },
      {
        "text": "son",
        "entity_key": "gnijr",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "still lives here, fitted out "
      },
      {
        "text": "a ship",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "and left for "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but failed to find any traces of her until his third trip, when he was rewarded with a footprint of a slender foot in the sand. For days "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was searched, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was found. "
      },
      {
        "text": "After attempting to flee, she changed her mind and received each with dignity.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She was brought to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and placed in the care of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. Nidever's Spanish wife",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She could speak only in sign language, as there were few, if any, of "
      },
      {
        "text": "her own tribe",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "living then on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_socalcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Before a month had elapsed, her new life and mode of living so affected her that she became ill and died. Just before she died, "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the mission fathers",
        "entity_key": "jru",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "christened her "
      },
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and she was buried in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "old mission grounds",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Juana Maria",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had pictured to ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Mrs. Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "through signs, that ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "probably had been killed by wild dogs before she could leave ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the ship",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "which first attempted to remove her from ",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          10
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}